---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Verified Software"
  description="About verifiedsoftware.dev: a practitioner-oriented resource tracking the convergence of AI and formal verification."
>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto">
      <span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-4 block fade-up">About</span>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-10 fade-up">What this is</h1>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed fade-up">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text-primary">Verified Software</strong> is a practitioner-oriented resource tracking the convergence of AI and formal verification. We cover the tools, techniques, and teams building software that is mathematically proven correct — not just tested.
        </p>
        <p>
          The verified software movement is accelerating, but information is scattered across academic papers, Zulip channels, and social media threads. We consolidate the signal: new research, production deployments, ecosystem developments, and practical guidance for engineering teams evaluating formal methods.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site is for CTOs, engineering leads, security engineers, and anyone building software where correctness matters. Whether you're running a fintech platform, maintaining critical infrastructure, or just curious about where the industry is headed — we aim to be the most useful source on what's happening and what it means.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is an independent publication, not affiliated with any vendor, research lab, or tool provider. We cover the ecosystem as we see it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
